defaulttwo people operating in partnership. It is recognised at various levels that they certainly have to be treated differently. For example, HMRC operates a very different stance and approach to taxing firms like PricewaterhouseCoopers compared to the two-person partnership. You would expect that, and the whole compliance cycle tends to be very different. That is partly a response to the sheer size and amount of money that is going through.
