defaultthat 
defaultthat is an argument, and that therefore perhaps the best way is to allow people to write to their MPs or whatever about it, but it should be possible to get past that and do a proper evaluation of how it has gone. If I can keep using the statutory residence test as an example, it would be difficult to do that just by expecting letters to MPs, because you ought to be 
